"528","<FILENAME>acctpron032.txt"
"529","<TEXT>"
"530","77L New accounting pronouncements"
"531","In May 2011, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB)"
"532","issued Accounting Standards Update (ASU) 2011 04 Fair Value"
"533","Measurements and Disclosures (Topic 820)  Amendments to Achieve"
"534","Common Fair Value Measurement and Disclosure Requirements in U.S."
"535","GAAP and IFRS. ASU 2011 04 amends FASB Topic 820 Fair Value"
"536","Measurement and seeks to develop common requirements for"
"537","measuring fair value and for disclosing information about fair"
"538","value measurements in accordance with GAAP. ASU 2011 04 is"
"539","effective for fiscal years and interim periods beginning after"
"540","December 15, 2011. The application of ASU 2011 04 did not have a"
"541","material impact on the funds financial statements."
"542","In December 2011, the FASB issued ASU No. 2011 11 Disclosures"
"543","about Offsetting Assets and Liabilities. The update creates new"
"544","disclosure requirements requiring entities to disclose both gross"
"545","and net information for derivatives and other financial"
"546","instruments that are either offset in the Statement of assets and"
"547","liabilities or subject to an enforceable master netting"
"548","arrangement or similar agreement. The disclosure requirements are"
"549","effective for annual reporting periods beginning on or after"
"550","January 1, 2013 and interim periods within those annual periods."
"551","Putnam Management is currently evaluating the application of ASU"
"552","2011 11 and its impact, if any, on the funds financial"
"553","statements."
"554","</TEXT>"
"555","</DOCUMENT>"
"556","<DOCUMENT>"
"557","<TYPE>EX-99"
"558","<SEQUENCE>3"
"559","<FILENAME>auditletter032.txt"
"560","<TEXT>"
"561","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm"
"562","The Board of Trustees and Shareholders"
"563","Putnam U.S. Government Income Trust:"
"564","In planning and performing our audit of the financial statements"
"565","of the Putnam U.S. Government  Income Trust (the Fund) as of and"
"566","for the year ended September 30, 2012, in accordance with the"
"567","standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board"
"568","(United States), we considered the Funds internal control over"
"569","financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding"
"570","securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures for"
"571","the purpose of expressing our opinion on the financial statements"
"572","and to comply with the requirements of Form NSAR, but not for the"
"573","purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the"
"574","Funds internal control over financial reporting.   Accordingly,"
"575","we express no such opinion."
"576","Management of the Fund is responsible for establishing and"
"577","maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting."
"578","In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and judgments by"
"579","management are required to assess the expected benefits and"
"580","related costs of controls.  A companys internal control over"
"581","financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable"
"582","assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and"
"583","the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in"
"584","accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. A"
"585","companys internal control over financial reporting includes those"
"586","policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of"
"587","records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect"
"588","the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the company;"
"589","(2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded"
"590","as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"591","accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and"
"592","that receipts and expenditures of the company are being made only"
"593","in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of"
"594","the company; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding"
"595","prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use,"
"596","or disposition of the companys assets that could have a material"
"597","effect on the financial statements."
"598","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over"
"599","financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements."
"600","Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future"
"601","periods are subject to the risk that controls may become"
"602","inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree"
"603","of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate."
"604","A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting exists"
"605","when the design or operation of a control does not allow"
"606","management or employees, in the normal course of performing their"
"607","assigned functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a"
"608","timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency, or a"
"609","combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial"
"610","reporting, such that there is a reasonable possibility that a"
"611","material misstatement of a Funds annual or interim financial"
"612","statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely basis."
"613","Our consideration of the Funds internal control over financial"
"614","reporting was for the limited purpose described in the first"
"615","paragraph and would not necessarily disclose all deficiencies in"
"616","internal control that might be material weaknesses under"
"617","standards established by the Public Company Accounting Oversight"
"618","Board (United States).  However, we noted no deficiencies in the"
"619","Funds internal control over financial reporting and its"
"620","operation, including controls over safeguarding securities that"
"621","we consider to be a material weakness as defined above as of"
"622","September 30, 2012."
